Defendant Chad W Bishop in court with attorney Paul Bugenhagen.  Bryan C. Bayer appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense requests adjournment of sentencing so defendant can help with fiancee.  Court denies request to adjourn.  Recommendations by the State.  Arguments by the Defense.  Statement by defendant.  Defense requests right to a hearing on defendant's ability to pay restitution.

The Court Orders the Following:

Count 1:
Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:
6 months Huber (Credit - 0 days) HUBER WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS.  CONSECUTIVE to any current sentence.

Term of Probation: 2 Years
Conditions of Probation:
-	AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
-	Mental Health Evaluation and follow through with any treatment recommended;
-	Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
-	No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
-	No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
-	Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
-	Inform agent of all prescriptions;
-	Sign Medical Release for Agent;
-	Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
-           Obtain a Valid Drivers License within first 90 days of Probation
-	Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
-	Maintain/Obtain full time employment;
-	No contact with codefendant
-            No contact with Spring Garden Landscaping or any of it's employees
Restitution: to be determined at Restitution hearing
Fine or Costs: $ 253.00
DNA Surcharge:  $ 200.00
(To to be paid at the rate of $60.00  per month commencing June 1, 2015 as a Condition of Probation).

Condition Time: 30 days - NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS - To commence by March 4, 2015 at 12:00 pm at the latest. 

Count 2:
Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:
6 months Huber (Credit - 0 days) HUBER WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS.  CONSECUTIVE to Count 1 and to any current sentence.

Term of Probation: 2 Years
Conditions of Probation:
-              Same as Count 1
Fine or Costs: $ 243.00
DNA Surcharge:  $ 200.00
(To to be paid at the rate of $60.00  per month commencing June 1, 2015 as a Condition of Probation).
